survey_response.review_text: A very good experience, she explains the root cause and provides appropriate treatment. Would definitely recommend to anyone experiencing allergic reactions.

I recently visited Dr. Shilpa to discuss my severe allergic reaction history, as I was concerned about traveling abroad. She was incredibly helpful and reassuring, explaining all the emergency measures I should take in case of a severe reaction when hospitals may not be readily available in a foreign land. 

Additionally, she provided me with all the necessary documentation to carry my medicines. Thanks to her guidance and support, I now feel confident and less worried about managing my severe allergy while traveling abroad. Thank you, Doctor!

Both the doctor as well as the nurse Mrs.Kushalkar were equally cordial and professional. I was able to explain my issues based on which a detailed allergy test was conducted. Subsequent to the outcome of the test, customised medicine would be provided (not immediately. I am told to come and collect or they can courier it) The doc gave a lucid explanation of the diagnosis results and how it can be arrested. She will proceed only once the patient is throughly convinced with the treatment. I can only comment about the outcome once my treatment starts.

I suffer from allergies both food and environmental. I came to India for a short visit and my allergies flared up. I googled online and I found Dr. Nayak. She has been treating me for over 8 months. My experience with her has been amazing.  She is such a wonderful person, takes her time to explain your illness with you in details. I had my allergy test done at her clinic and that was painless !! I have a phobia for needles and they took great care to give me a pain free experience.  I would highly recommend her to anyone who has issues with allergies.

I went in for cat dander immunotherapy. The doctor just wanted to give me medication for 3 to 6 months *** **** ***** ******** She said no to giving 1 month medicine to start with. ****** *************** *****

Did not even do a physical checkup of my child who is suffering from consistent cough and runny nose.  She looked to hurry in and recommend some tests  for further investigation.. Which looked a bit strange. I was looking to expect  a detailed  assessment considering that she is a specialist some quality inputs and willingness to address concerns of the parents. I had an excellent experience sitting down with Dr. Shilpa and discussing various things about my current situation and how they all relate to allergies. If any of you are suffering from any allergies or allergy related issues like autoimmune diseases, getting an opinion from Dr. Shilpa is highly recommended.

Had a very very lovely and informative experience with Dr. Shilpa,  would definitely recommend her to whoever needed.
